article.headline: Wyoming 68, TCU 64
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Daaron Brown scored 19 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Wyoming past TCU 68-64 on Saturday night. Nile Murry's 3-pointer trimmed Wyoming's lead to one with 1:33 left, but Kevin Lewis blocked Murry's potential go-ahead jumper with 19 seconds left. Brad Jones added 18 and Brandon Ewing had 14 for Wyoming (8-7, 1-1 Mountain West). Chudi Chinweze scored 17 points, including 15 in the second half, to lead TCU (4-11, 0-1). Murry finished with 15. Wyoming trailed by four at halftime but outscored the Frogs 18-5 over the final 6:14.
